<item>
            <title>[LU-19526] iov_iter_is_aligned() should be checking actual buffer address</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19526</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;reading iov_iter_is_aligned() I noticed the following code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; inline bool iov_iter_is_aligned(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; struct iov_iter *i,
				       unsigned addr_mask, unsigned len_mask)
{
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (likely(iter_is_ubuf(i))) {
		&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (i-&amp;gt;count &amp;amp; len_mask)
			&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
		&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((unsigned &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;)(iter_iov(i) + i-&amp;gt;iov_offset) &amp;amp; addr_mask)
			&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;notice iter_iov&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; returns struct iovec *, not address of the data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="93203">LU-19526</key>
            <summary>iov_iter_is_aligned() should be checking actual buffer address</summary>
