                            <comment id="476337" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2025 03:56:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Shaun Tancheff &amp;lt;shaun.tancheff@hpe.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62068&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62068&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19526&quot; title=&quot;iov_iter_is_aligned() should be checking actual buffer address&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19526&quot;&gt;LU-19526&lt;/a&gt; compat: provide iov_iter ubuf accessor&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 56ecb21b4ac9cd078580c0fb61322d2c18878ce0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476335" author="stancheff" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2025 03:34:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah .. it passed the compiler but is kind of non-sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the &apos;iter_is_ubuf()&apos; and the iov_iter member ubuf arrived in the same commit:&lt;br/&gt;
   v5.19-10287-gfcb14cb1bdac &lt;br/&gt;
And &apos;iov: introduce iov_iter_aligned()&apos; arrived around the same time:&lt;br/&gt;
   v5.19-rc4-8-gcfa320f72882&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we have probably never seen a case where iter_is_ubuf() arrived without iov_iter_aligned() and the code in question has never been executed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the best fix is provide an #define accessor for iter-&amp;gt;ubuf() to satisfy the compiler so the code is sensible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it should have been:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;	if (likely(iter_is_ubuf(i))) {
		if (i-&amp;gt;count &amp;amp; len_mask)
			return false;
		if ((unsigned long)(i-&amp;gt;ubuf + i-&amp;gt;iov_offset) &amp;amp; addr_mask)
			return false;
		return true;
	}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But ubuf does not exist so the compiler chokes, so instead:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;#ifdef HAVE_USER_BACKED_ITER
#define iter_ubuf(iter)			((iter)-&amp;gt;ubuf)
#else
#define iter_ubuf(iter)			(0ul) /* unused */
#endif /* HAVE_USER_BACKED_ITER */

	if (likely(iter_is_ubuf(i))) {
		if (i-&amp;gt;count &amp;amp; len_mask)
			return false;
		if ((unsigned long)(iter_ubuf(i) + i-&amp;gt;iov_offset) &amp;amp; addr_mask)
			return false;
		return true;
	}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;tt&gt;((iter)&lt;del&gt;&amp;gt;__iov&lt;/del&gt;&amp;gt;iov_base)&lt;/tt&gt; would be the closest approximation to ubuf here but there really isn&apos;t any need since ubuf and iter_is_ubuf() are synonymous here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476297" author="paf0186" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2025 19:02:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it should be using iter_iov&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;-&amp;gt;iov_base?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also this is a nice reminder of how terrible type checking is in C (not anyone&apos;s fault here).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476294" author="bzzz" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2025 18:01:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stancheff&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stancheff&quot;&gt;stancheff&lt;/a&gt; can you please check?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
